The paper deals with visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach to improve the accuracy of Siamese network based trackers by using deep networks such as ResNet-50, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses model architecture and aggregation techniques, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
